Installation
============

Prerequisites
-------------

First, install the python prerequisites::

    $ pip install -r requirements.txt

If you want to run your own version of the API (for testing purposes), you'll need MongoDb

You can clone the repo with all Living Labs Challenge's code as follows::

    $ git clone git@bitbucket.org:aschuth/ll-challenge.git


Building Documentation
----------------------

To build the docs::
    
    $ cd docs
    $ rm -r build && make html

The documentation will appear in docs/build/html.
